<L>__{ext garden day}
<A>__{...and we find them in discussion by the fountain:}
<C>__{elizabeth}
<D>__{what sort of task?}
<C>__{victor}
<D>__{it's not something i can explain now. perhaps someday.}
<C>__{elizabeth}
<D>__{what of our marriage? victor, we've had so much tragedy. i want this family to live again.}
<C>__{victor}
<D>__{so do i.}
<C>__{elizabeth}
<D>__{we need each other now, i need your comfort and strength, not separation and solitude.}
<C>__{victor}
<D>__{a month at most, that's all i ask.}
<P>__{(draws close)}
<D>__{elizabeth, please. things have not yet resolved. i must take steps to see that they do. for our family's sake. for our sake.}
<P>__{(caresses her face)}
<D>__{you are life itself. we shall seal our vow. the moment i am done.}
<A>__{he leans forward to kiss her... and pauses, hearing the distant music of a recorder echoing from the hills...}
